This might be the wrong place to ask this question, but the Nodejitsu IRC channel did'nt provide too much help except that they did see drones having SPDY. So, sorry if this is the wrong place.

Anyhow; I'm trying to get an Express app to run at Nodejitsu with SPDY support. I have SSL set up for the app by doing the default setup by uploading the SSL certificates in the Nodejitsu admin interface so the Nodejitsu loadbalancer / proxy appends the SSL. That is working fine.

Though, from what I've understood after reading the [docs](https://github.com/indutny/node-spdy#options) and [misc issues](https://github.com/indutny/node-spdy/issues/107) is that in such circumstances the SPDY server should be set to ```plain : true``` and ```ssl : false```.  

iow; my app looks more or less like this:

```js
var express = require('express');
var spdy = require('spdy');
var app = express();

// app config and misc routes etc.

var options = {
  plain: true,
  ssl: false
};
var server = spdy.createServer(options, app);
server.listen(8000);
```

Though; when deploying this at Nodejitsu, SPDY is not enabled. I there something I'm missing in this set up in the app side?

Is there a known way to get SPDY working on Nodejitsu?

