@misterdjules spdy optimizes web page loading -- to load many resources over a single TCP/IP pipe. The typical client grabs only a single resource, which is effectively the same thing as requesting a single resource over HTTP/1.0.  

The only time that I've used a command line spdy client is for testing and experimenting. Personally, I use https://github.com/tatsuhiro-t/spdylay for such cases. Between that and other clients (like the one from nasss), I do not see a strong need for a client in this project.

Even so, I'm sure something will get added in here at some point, but I don't see a compelling reason for that to happen imminently.

